wikipedia_page.main: Group Captain Reginald Stuart Maxwell,  (20 July 1894 – 1 July 1960) was a British flying ace during World War I. He continued in RAF service until 1941, and served in the RNVR during World War II.

response: * Sir Reginald Maxwell (civil servant) (1882–1967), British administrator in India
* Reginald Maxwell (RAF officer) (1894–1960), British flying ace during World War I
